RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NIXA raced four wide through the first turn when pressing the leader, cleared when straightening in the lane, widened through late turn and continued to lengthen the advantage to the wire. EMERSON'S DREAM raced in the three or four path through the far turn, came into the lane three wide, was nearest the winner through the lane, could not gain on that one but stayed on to save the place spot. MISS DIAMOND RICH chased the pace from the three path into the turn, was closest the winner in late turn, shuffled back when passed on both sides into the lane, reengaged while shifting into the seven path and moved up. LEGS FOR DAYS vied for the lead through the first turn while along the inside, continued along the rail into the lane when never far back and weakened. RAISE N PRAISE pressed the early pace three wide through the first turn, continued to chase the pace into the far turn then dropped back, was in the seven path into the lane, drifted in to the three path and was no a threat late. SEQUEEKER pressed the pace while two wide early, continued to chase the winner while in the two path into the turn, dropped back and was eased through the lane and returned bleeding from the nostrils and was vanned off.

ENTRY.NAME: Legs for Days
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied early inside, chased rail, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Sequeeker
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2wd early, done turn, eased lane, bled, vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Nixa
ENTRY.OWNER: Three Star Stable King Robert W Strahan Karen Strahan James and Haynes Chuck

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 76. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COPPERLITE chased the pace from the three path into the far turn, continued to move closer to the pacesetter through the turn, took over into the lane from the two path when leader faltered, cleared outside the eighth pole and was under a drive to hold. FINN MCSORLEY was in the two path through the first turn when unhurried, continued near the inside into the far turn when shuffled back to trail, was asked for more leaving the bend, angled into the six path and was rolling late while drifting in a couple of paths and ran out of time. BADGE OF WAR saved ground through the turn, cut the corner and continued a serious threat, came off the inside to pass a tiring rival near the eighth pole, continued on with good energy to be gaining at the end. YELLOW JACKET was along the inside through late turn when never far back, came into the lane three wide, had aim on the top ones but needed more late. FINN AND BRENNAN raced in the four path through the turns when near the back, swung into the lane from the five or six path and offered a mild gain. JAILHOUSE JUSTICE pressed the pace two wide, lost momentum into the lane and weakened. GOOD POINT never a factor while along the inside. WOODFORD HOLLER set the pace along the inside while under pressure then faded along the inside through the lane. DOUBLE GOLD never a factor while saving ground. CALL EM KARL raced in the four path through the turns and was empty into the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: YOLO SANTIAGO stalked the pace in the three path, bid at the three-eighths pole, went clear in the stretch and lasted under strong urging. CHARLIE WHISKEY raced in the four path, rallied at the three-sixteenths pole, closed but couldn't get past the winner. HASKELLED stalked the pace inside, bid at the quarter pole but faltered. BOULDER BAY was unrushed in the two path, bid at the three-sixteenths pole but couldn't close late. FIRST CROWNED was clear early but gave way in the stretch. CARTOON CAPER stalked the pace between rivals, then gave way. SCHENECTADY STAR was no factor while in the four path.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 82. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 1 mile and 70 yards on the main track.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CABLE BOSS was in mid-pack while in mid-pack, bid into the lane from the three or four path, drifted into the six path then back into the four path when gaining serious momentum and was up in time from the three path. SATURDAY LONG LEGS set the pace on a clear lead through the turn and into the lane, had his largest advantage with an eighth to go, was joined by the winner in deep stretch and gave ground grudgingly. POLYGLOT chased the pace along the inside into the lane, moved into the two path for the drive and was finishing with the winner and missed between. COACH PETRO raced in the two path while near the back, came off the inside through mid-turn, continued with momentum into the lane while angling to the six path, continued willingly from mid-track and was closing in. SMART PRIZE was unhurried while off the rail into the turn, was three wide into the lane, continued in the three path for the final eighth and was gaining to the wire. LYTE CRUDE saved ground through the turn and into the lane, was still a threat and lost positions late. SIX MISSIONS raced in the three or four path through the turn and into the lane and lacked the needed response. TEXAS TOAST raced three wide through the first turn, continued into the three path through the far turn and tired turning into the lane. HILTON HEAD chased the pace from the two or three path into the far turn. SERPA was outrun while near the inside. OPERATORE PAZZO was getting out through the first turn and into the backstretch, dropped back into the far turn and was never in it.

ENTRY.COMMENT: mid-pack, 2path, bid 4path upper, drifted in/out, in time
